{
  "stem": "6777.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's a special name for it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish police force.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Headed by Szerynski who was before the war very high in the Polish police.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, he was in the French Legion.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know what the French Legion was?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he also committed suicide once he got to know what awaits and what was asked from him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To-- to the Judenrat and through the Judenrat to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And maybe directly, I can't really tell you exactly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because that was out of my reach.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I haven't been the right to know all the details of this relationship between.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "SS men.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had a pass and the permission to go into the Polish side without the armband, and I made good use of it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can assure you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because they'd been embarrassed, the Germans, that a Jew came to their buildings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was embarrassing for them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, they knew I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they'd been embarrassed to have a Jewish person coming to their buildings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, all sorts of things-- different things to different people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We started to plan of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To live as Poles on the Polish side.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because it was evident that the ghetto would not last forever.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And because I had the permission to move without the armband and because I was bilingual in German-- although I rode in the German part of the Polish tramways.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I hired a flat on the Polish side, and we brought out the grandma and the kids, Roman and Eva.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember quite.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the children, Roman and Eva, they'd been taken-- and Vera-- they went all together to Otwock, which was a Jewish mental hospital.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Which was fairly big.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
